-- Alitalia to Join Air France-KLM, Delta Joint Venture, Les Echos Reports
-- Andrew Roberts
-- 2010-07-05T06:31:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-05/alitalia-to-join-air-france-klm-delta-joint-venture-les-echos-reports.html

          
          
             Alitalia plans to enter the joint
venture between  Air France-KLM Group  and  Delta Air Lines Inc. 
that cooperates on trans-Atlantic flights,  Les Echos  reported,
without saying where it got the information.  
 Alitalia Chief Executive Officer  Rocco Sabelli , Air France-
KLM CEO  Pierre-Henri Gourgeon  and Delta CEO  Richard Anderson 
will announce the deal today at a press conference in Rome, the
newspaper said.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
 Andrew Roberts  in Paris at 
 aroberts36@bloomberg.net .  
          
          


  


        